Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Financial Analyst - Full-time, Non-union position NEWMARKET , ON Description Overview of positionUnder the direction of the Manager, Library Operations, the Financial Analyst is responsible for developing financial analysis and reports, coordinating and monitoring the capital and operating budgets, maintaining fixed asset program, coordinating statistics, researching and recommending financial policies and procedures/statutory requirements, coordinating grant applications, and liaising with and responding to staff.Duties and Responsibilities1. Post secondary degree in Accounting, Business Administration, Commerce, Economics or related discipline and currently enrolled in a recognized professional accounting designation (CPA) program at an intermediate level or equivalent is required. An equivalent combination of education and experience will be considered.2. Experience in a Non-profit accounting environment is an asset.3. Demonstrated experience in financial planning, activity based costing, reporting and analysis.4. Experience with internal controls, auditing and budgets.5. Working knowledge of computerized accounting system, as well as intermediate spreadsheet and introductory word processing software. 6. Ability to work independently in a team setting, be a self-starter and be able to organize and prioritize work to meet deadlines.7. Ability to deal courteously and effectively with all levels of staff.8. Well-developed analytical, problem solving, communication and interpersonal skills.Credentials Required1. Post secondary degree in Accounting, Business Administration, Commerce, Economics or related discipline and currently enrolled in a recognized professional accounting designation (CPA) program at an intermediate level or equivalent is required. An equivalent combination of education and experience will be considered.2. Experience in a Non-profit accounting environment is an asset.3. Demonstrated experience in financial planning, activity based costing, reporting and analysis.4. Experience with internal controls, auditing and budgets.5. Working knowledge of computerized accounting system, as well as intermediate spreadsheet and introductory word processing software. 6. Ability to work independently and in a team setting, be a self-starter and be able to organize and prioritize work to meet deadlines.7. Ability to deal courteously and effectively with all levels of staff.8. Well-developed analytical, problem solving, communication and interpersonal skills.Due to the responsibilities of this position, a Police Record Check satisfactory to the Newmarket Public Library is required.Hours of work 35 hours a week including evening and weekend shifts,Submit a cover letter and resume at Deltek Talent Management - Financial Analyst (NPL) - (24-89) (hrsmart.com).We thank all applicants for their interest. However, only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Newmarket Public Library is committed to accommodating all applicants in accordance with the Ontario Human Rights Code for all employment activities including the recruitment process. The Newmarket Public Library is committed to a barrier-free recruitment and selection process. We uphold our values of diversity, equity, inclusion and anti-racism in the delivery of our services and in our workplace. The Library encourages applications from all applicants, including members of groups with historical employment barriers to equity, this is including but not limited to, Indigenous, Black and Racialized Groups, People with Disabilities, Women and Persons within the 2SLGBTQ+ community. Compensation $70,579 - $84,023 Closes: 21 May, 2024 Newmarket Public Library - Employees NEWMARKET , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
