Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Provincial Cataloguing Technician Regina , SK Description The Saskatchewan Ministry of Education provides leadership and direction to Saskatchewan’s education, early years, library and literacy sectors. The ministry is committed to providing equitable and inclusive education, early years and library systems that benefit all learners. It foundationally places Indigenous knowledge systems, cultures and languages within structures, policies and curricula. The Ministry of Education is advancing reconciliation with early years, Prekindergarten to Grade 12, library, and First Nations, Métis and Inuit partners by acknowledging our shared history to build a brighter future together.The Ministry of Education, Provincial Library &amp; Literacy Office (PLLO) requires a dedicated and well-organized individual to fill a role as a Provincial Cataloguing Technician. Reporting to the Manager of Library Network Development (LND), the Provincial Cataloguing Technician will assist in supporting and providing guidance to the unit in a number of areas, including cataloguing, maintenance of the data integrity of the Library Systems database, and the training of other staff. Typical duties will include:Review cataloguing for the regional library systems in an accurate and timely manner while ensuring that all cataloguing conforms to accepted cataloguing guidelines;Provide unit statistics and run any requested reports in the Integrated Library System software;In consultation with the LND manager, establish work priorities for unit staff and suggest/implement workflow changes;Oversee batch editing of e-record loads to ensure quality and consistency of data;Provide data quality assurance by troubleshooting, error correction and data cleaning in the SILS bibliographic database;Provide original cataloguing to unique materials that have no source records from remote databases. This may include but is not limited to: local history items, kits, three dimensional objects or serials;Provide needed advice to regional libraries on item creation in the Integrated Library System database;Provide advice and guidance on cataloguing issues and troubleshooting to the public library sector; andParticipation in bibliographic related library sector committees as needed.The ideal candidate will have:Experience cataloguing a wide variety of library materials in the MARC21 standard;Knowledge of Library of Congress and Dewey Decimal subject headings;Experience in the supervision of staff;Knowledge of Integrated Library System software; andExperience working with spreadsheet software.Typically, qualifications for this position would be obtained through the completion of a library technician diploma which includes knowledge of metadata principles and integrated library systems. Other candidates may be considered based upon their education and experience. What We Offer: Dynamic, challenging work;A competitive salary;Comprehensive benefits package including pension;Vacation, earned days off (EDOs) and other types of leave;Inclusive work environments; andAdvancement opportunities.Preference will be given to qualified equity group members who self-declare in this online application, as identified in "diversity groups" belowDiversity Groups: Aboriginal persons, Persons with disabilitiesHours of Work: A - SGEU Office 36 - one day off every two weeksNumber of Openings1Closing Date May 15, 2024, 11:59:00 PMApply Here at: https://govskpsc.taleo.net/careersection/10040/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&amp;job=LIB000359 Compensation 26.038 - 32.630 Hourly Closes: 15 May, 2024 Provincial Library &amp; Literacy Office Regina , SK Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
